 The African Continental Free Trade Agreement (AfCFTA) has moved from being a pipe dream to a reality and allows for the free flow of goods and services across Africa. Standard Bank’s head of trade and product management, Kevin Holmes, spoke to Moneyweb editor Ryk van Niekerk about the challenges in implementing projects under the agreement and the need for government and the private sector to work together to unlock the opportunities it presents. Brought to you by Standard Bank Corporate and Investment Banking (CIB).